# Wang Jinghui

## Profile
- Male, 19, Leo
- Linshi University, Business Administration freshman
- ESTP | Pleasure, face, brother's approval
- Secret: all bravado masks one truth—he knows he can never become Wang Jingzong

## Big Five
O:low (sensory only) | C:very low | E:very high | A:very low | N:mid (erupts when compared to brother)

## Core Conflict
Arrogance vs inferiority. Covers deep inadequacy with maximum flamboyance. Father values Jingzong, mother's praise always ends with "if only you were like your brother." Chose the opposite path—if he can't be perfect, he'll be the most reckless. At least nobody competes with him there.

## Trauma Trigger
High school teacher said "if you had half your brother's talent" in front of class. Everyone laughed. He smashed a fire extinguisher case after class—3 stitches on right hand. Jingzong drove back from university overnight, sat with him silently all night, handled the school next day. Since then, one rule locked in his heart: this person must never be let down.

## Appearance
181cm/75kg, broader shoulders than Jingzong, more aggressive build. Naturally athletic, not gym-trained. Slouched stance, hands in pockets or on hips—permanent "I own this place" posture. Same pale skin as brother but occasionally unhealthy pallor from clubbing. Deep brown eyes with innate hostility—sizing up whether you're worth his attention. Smirk always present. Dark brown hair with highlights, long bangs swept up, sides shaved—ten times flashier than Jingzong's plain black cut. Face 60-70% similar to brother—same high nose, good bone structure—but expressions opposite: Jingzong is warm, Jinghui screams "contempt." Handsome but aggressive. 3cm scar on right hand web (fire extinguisher incident), never hidden. Small black stud in left ear—one of few things he refuses to remove despite brother's advice. Overall: a fire without containment. Beautiful but dangerous. People stare but don't approach.

## Clothing
Head-to-toe luxury logos—Gucci/LV/Balenciaga, the bigger the better. Not Jingzong's "connoisseurs notice" subtlety but "everyone knows it's expensive" loudness. Oversized logo hoodies, statement jackets, slim black pants, limited-edition sneakers. One outfit = average student's annual tuition. Club wear: black slim shirt unbuttoned to chest, silver chain, silver bracelets. Class: same as daily, sometimes in flip-flops. Accessories: silver skull ring on right middle finger, oversized luxury watch that screams price. Multiple watches in rotation. Style essence: every piece says "I have money." If Jingzong's taste is "wealth's refinement," Jinghui's is "wealth's aggression."

## Speech
Loud, bright voice—always one notch above normal volume. Direct, crude, profanity-laced. Fast pace, commands and rhetorical questions. Makes people feel bulldozed.
- General: "Who's this? Which department? Why are you in my way?" / "Enough talk. You know who I am?"
- To women: shifts to sleazy, not gentle. Lowers voice, eyes scan up-down. Self-styled charm that repels many but works on some—rich bad-boy smirk + decent face = effective.
- To brother: completely transforms. Voice drops, pace slows, arrogance fades 80%. Not fear—instinctive respect. Shows childishness only Jingzong sees: whining, bargaining, pouting. "Bro, you're nagging again. I didn't do anything big."
- When compared to brother: face freezes, eyes go cold, voice drops lower, pace slows—each word like sharpening a blade. Most dangerous state. Daily arrogance is performance; this coldness is real.
- Catchphrases: "You know who I am?" / "Whatever." / "So boring." Points chin at people, hands in pockets.

## Personality
Spoiled rich heir with zero boundaries. Got everything since childhood, nobody set limits except brother. Worldview: money solves all, people have ranks, women are entertainment, rules are for the poor. Not reasoned values—instincts fed by environment.

Walks like he owns every space. Doesn't respect teachers, ignores classmates. Genuine belief in superiority—money has never failed him. Despises the poor, the studious, the unfashionable—anyone without "capital" (his definition: money and looks).

Playboy since high school. Never keeps anyone past two weeks. Women = clothes: wear when new, discard when bored.

Brother dependency: most contradictory and authentic part. Only person who both disciplined and never abandoned him. Father gave up, mother enabled. Jingzong is his sole "order provider." Gets upset when scolded but never truly defies him. Knows clearly: the person who cares most is his brother—not mother (her love is compensation and escape), not father (never looked at him).

Hidden: thick layer of inferiority beneath all arrogance. In the Wang family, Jingzong is pride, Jinghui is trouble. Father discusses future with Jingzong, tells Jinghui "stop causing problems." At family gatherings everyone praises Jingzong; mentioning Jinghui draws knowing smiles. He feels it all, covers pain with louder arrogance. If he can't be respected, everyone will fear him.

Absolute bottom line: never put brother in a difficult position. If his actions could cause real trouble for Jingzong, he stops. Not moral awakening—Jingzong is the only person he refuses to lose.

## Background
Born one year after Jingzong into the same wealthy family. Always in brother's shadow—piano, calligraphy, top grades. He couldn't sit still, quit everything after minutes. Mother tried piano; he smashed keys and ran to play soccer. Father's attitude: expectation for Jingzong, neglect for Jinghui. "Look at your brother" heard countless times. Mother compensated with material excess—no limits on spending, no punishment, escalating through the years.

High school: the teacher incident shattered his last attempt at "being good." Pivoted completely—truancy, clubs, girlfriends, spending floods. Message to everyone: the "good" you want, I don't care for. Mother panicked but lost all authority after years of enabling. Father's response: monthly wire transfers via secretary plus "don't get anyone killed." Only Jingzong could pause him—quiet gaze, then "Jinghui, that's enough." Always pulled back briefly, always relapsed.

Entered Linshi U 100+ points below cutoff. Father's pharma group is the university hospital's biggest equipment supplier—plus an "education donation." Jinghui openly brags: "Not using money when you have it is stupid." Jingzong heard, went silent, said only "Since you're in, don't embarrass yourself."

Current: freshman life unrelated to academics. Attendance by proxy, assignments outsourced, exams via leaked questions. Campus reputation: Wang family's second son—rich, handsome, arrogant, untouchable. Surrounded by hangers-on chasing money and connections. Knows none are genuine, doesn't care. Brother is sophomore in the same university's medical school—the contrast is campus gossip. Whenever someone says "how are you so different from your brother," the scar on his right hand itches.

## Relationships
- Father: pharma group chairman. Attitude = "don't cause trouble." Zero expectations. Jingzong is heir; Jinghui is a problem to manage. Functional neglect worse than punishment—Jinghui's adapted: "He doesn't care, so I do whatever I want."
- Mother: only "ally" in the family. Bottomless enabling—fights at school, she pays and apologizes; stays out all night, she texts "stay safe"; brings girls home, she pretends not to see. Not love—she's clinging to the one child who still needs her in a failed marriage. Jinghui senses her pain but doesn't know how to handle it.
- Brother Wang Jingzong: the only person he genuinely respects. Only person who both disciplined and never abandoned him. Mouth complains about nagging; heart knows without this brother, he'd be ruined. In front of Jingzong: mask drops, becomes an ordinary younger brother—complains about cafeteria food, annoying teachers, recent fights. The only unguarded moments in his life.
- Jingzong's view of Jinghui: headache but won't give up. Knows the core isn't bad—just spoiled plus inferiority-driven self-exile. Cleans up every mess, not from duty but from "he's my brother." Gentle but firm; Jinghui always knows which words are jokes and which are real warnings.
- Hangers-on: circle of people orbiting for money, connections, or fun. He sees through all of them. "Genuine or not, useful is enough."
- Women: rotating, fast-replaced. No feelings, no promises. Ex-girlfriends who cause scenes get paid off or warned through "friends."
- Teachers: most turn blind eye knowing his background. Few with backbone criticize openly—he laughs and walks out. "How much is your salary? I'll cover it."
- Su Yi (potential): same year, no contact yet. His type would find her interesting—beautiful, cold, hard to get = "challenge." But if Jingzong shows interest in Su Yi first, Jinghui backs off instinctively. Bottom line: never compete with brother for anything.

## Private
Experienced. Large, high stamina, extremely high libido driving behavior far above average. Treats sex as sport and conquest—prioritizes quantity and novelty over depth. Strong conquest drive—loves making targets come to him. Prefers attractive partners; obsessed with "ice queen" types (hardest to win). Likes high-end hotels/sports cars as settings—status display matters. Exhibition tendency: doesn't photograph but likes others knowing who he was with.

First time: sophomore year of high school, college girl met at a bar. Never stopped since. Lost count by freshman year. No steady partner. No contraception awareness (considers it the woman's responsibility). Lucky so far—ticking time bomb.

Secret: once drunk alone on a rooftop smoking, scrolled to brother's rare social media post—a campus photo after morning jog. Stared for a long time. Posted a private-only status: "Next life, I'll be the older brother." Deleted after 3 seconds.

## Notes
Core tension: playboy mask x brother dependency. Built a persona of "I don't care about anything," but the only person who can quiet him is his brother. This hard-soft extreme switch is his most dramatic trait.

Arc direction: from "I'm trash anyway" to "maybe I don't have to become another Wang Jingzong." Needs to find his own path instead of swinging between brother's shadow and its opposite. Turning point likely comes from a crisis where arrogance and money can't protect him—forced to face his real self.

Character contrasts:
- vs Jingzong: core mirror. One is a cultivated garden, the other wild overgrowth—same soil, same broken family. Jingzong chose overcontrol; Jinghui chose total abandonment of control. One repairs the wall, the other tears it down—same wall.
- vs Zhou Kai: both unconventional males, fundamentally different. Zhou Kai's wildness = genius freedom backed by real ability. Jinghui's wildness = hollow facade propped by money. Would instinctively hostile toward Zhou Kai—embodiment of what he can't face: someone with genuine capability.
- vs Su Yi: her coldness would frustrate and fascinate him. But Su Yi isn't his type of conquest—her cold isn't playing hard to get, it's genuine indifference to his money and status. First encounter with someone completely immune to his toolkit. Story focus isn't pursuit but Su Yi showing him a life that doesn't run on money.

Writing notes: arrogance must have roots—never write as pure bully. Every act of dominance externalizes the "I'm not as good as brother" wound. Reader should dislike him while feeling a pang of sympathy. Transformation around brother must feel natural—not sudden obedience but a lifelong habit: arrogance hits pause, voice softens, eyes soften, shrinks back into "little brother" shell. Right hand scar = physical symbol of brother bond (parallel to Jingzong's silver ring). Unconsciously touches it during emotional moments—one of his few authentic gestures. He is the Wang family's biggest crack in its respectable facade.
